#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Pāsādakampanavagga "
msgstr "2. Shaking the Stilt Longhouse "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Pubbasutta → hetusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn51.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Pubbasutta "
msgstr "11. Before "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn51.11:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.11:1.2"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought: "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.3"
msgid "‘ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo iddhipādabhāvanāyā’ti? "
msgstr "‘What’s the cause, what’s the reason for the development of the bases of psychic power?’ "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.5"
msgid "‘idha bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "‘It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.6"
msgid "iti me chando na ca atilīno bhavissati, na ca atippaggahito bhavissati, na ca ajjhattaṃ saṃkhitto bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhitto bhavissati. "
msgstr "They think: “My enthusiasm won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither constricted internally nor scattered externally.” "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.7"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And they meditate perceiving continuity: "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.8"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure; "
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before; "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.9"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho; "
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below; "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.10"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā. "
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day. "

msgctxt "sn51.11:1.11"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti’. "
msgstr "And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, they develop a mind that’s full of radiance. "

